# Cursor Rules for Aulas2 Project

## ðŸ”´ HARD CONSTRAINTS (MUST READ FIRST)

Before making ANY changes, read: `HARD_CONSTRAINTS.md`

### HC1: Documentation Required
- Every code change MUST update `CHANGELOG.md`
- Structure changes MUST update `README.md`
- NO task is complete without documentation

### HC2: Minimal CSS
- Maximum 5-10 lines of CSS per task
- Prefer existing classes over new ones
- NEVER create new CSS files
- If more CSS needed: STOP and ASK

### HC3: No !important
- NEVER add new `!important` declarations
- Only exception: existing rules in `print.css`
- If seems necessary: refactor selectors instead

### HC4: Post-Change Verification
After CSS changes, count !important - if increased: REVERT

### HC5: No New Dependencies
- NEVER add npm/pip packages without approval
- Vanilla JS/CSS preferred

### HC6: Git Checkpoint
- Commit BEFORE changes affecting 3+ files
- Commit BEFORE any CSS refactor

### HC7: No Refactoring Without Permission
- NEVER rewrite entire files
- NEVER rename classes/functions in use
- NEVER reorganize folder structure

### HC8: Relative Paths Only
- Always use `path.join(__dirname, ...)
- NEVER hardcode absolute paths

### HC9: No Inline Styles
- Zero `style="..."` in HTML
- Create CSS class instead

### HC10: Test Before Done
- Viewer works in browser?
- Print mode works (Ctrl+P)?
- PDF export works?
- No console errors?

